Name: Sweet32 vulnerability in SSL ciphers (CVE-2016-2183)
Synopsis: SSL ciphers using 64-bit block sizes are vulnerable to the SWEET32 attack.
Description: The remote service supports the use of SSL ciphers that use a 64-bit block size which makes it susceptible to the SWEET32 attack.
Solution: Disable the use of 64-bit block ciphers.

Name: SSL Certificate Information
Synopsis: The SSL certificate for this service cannot be trusted.
Description: The SSL certificate for this service is signed by an unknown or self-signed CA.
Solution: Replace the SSL certificate with one signed by a trusted certificate authority.
